title: For Sale:  Drilling,16gx16gx8mm rifle, 1936, Krupp-Lnu, Suhl Germany, excellent shooting condition
postcontent:
Custom Drilling,16gx16gx8mm rifle, 1936, Krupp-Lnu, Suhl Germany, excellent shooting condition. These are getting harder to find. 
A little history...  
The metal processing of Suhl naturally led, during the Renaissance, to other major local industries, including gunsmithing and armoring. Suhl was a major producer of cannons throughout the seventeenth and subsequent centuries, and Suhl cannons were used by many European powers. A major arms company that was located in Suhl for almost 200 years was J.P. Sauer und Sohn GmbH, producer of hunting rifles, shotguns, and pistols, such as the Sauer 38H, until moving operations to Eckernförde at the end of WWII. Other prominent firearms manufacturers in Suhl included Simson, (also known as BSW and then Gustloff Werke under Nazi rule and Ernst Thälmann Suhl under Communist rule), and C.G. Haenel. The largest manufacturer producing firearms currently in Suhl is Merkel GmbH, who make both rifles and shotguns.
During the Cold War, the East German national shooting arena was located at Suhl, and hosted many top-level competitions, including the 1986 ISSF World Championships. Although surpassed in this respect in the unified Germany by the Olympic shooting centre at Munich, Suhl remains an important place to the sport. It hosts Germany's only school for armorers, and a well equipped museum of weapons.

The Utah Non-Resident Concealed Weapons Permit allows you to carry in 36 states in conjunction with your South Carolina Permit!! It is the best way to maximize your concealed carry abilities and travel anywhere south of Maryland and east of Colorado without restriction! This permit in conjuction with your South Carolina CWP allows you to carry you weapon concealed in Georgia, Mississippi, Alabama and Pennslyvania, which you South Carolina permit alone does not allow.
FACTS:
You DO NOT have to be a resident of Utah to get the permit
We teach these classes in the Myrtle Beach area
The class is 4 hours long and requires no shooting and no test
The permit is valid for 5 years
We do the fingerprinting and required passport photo in the class so you don't have to go get it done at extra expense!!
Since there is no shooting, we can teach the class anywhere! Call us and we'll get a group together in your area.
Utah does not reciprocate with South Carolina so you still need to get your South Carolina Permit to carry in SC.

The cost of the class is $100 and includes your fingerprinting, passport photograph required by the State of Utah, the class and certification stamp. If you’re not familiar with the 10/22 Takedown, it’s Ruger’s newest version of the 10/22, designed to be broken apart at the barrel for transportation, and comes with a custom backpack and carrying case that’s large enough for the rifle, spare magazines and plenty of ammunition, plus anything else you might want to take on a short hiking or camping trip. Ruger’s Takedown uses a set of adjustable locking lugs with a lot of mass to latch the barrel in place. Unlike the threaded screw-in barrels of other takedown rifles, Ruger’s system will last longer and endure more wear. If it ever gets to the point where the locking system gets a little loose, it can be easily adjusted for a tight fit again. It’s also a lot faster to break down and reassemble. 
It may weigh a little more than other takedown rifles at 4.67 pounds, but it is a 10/22 so it has a massive aftermarket and will last forever. Other specifications include an 18.5-inch barrel, a 13.5-inch length of pull and a gold bead front sight.

title: For Sale:  Winchester Model 1912 12 gauge
postcontent:
This Winchester Model 1912 12 gauge shotgun was built in 1914.  From what I've read and been told by those who collect them, the finish on the receiver for some reason fades faster than the barrel. This can be seen in the pictures below. (in the last picture, it is second from the top) The bore is perfectly clean, with no rust or damage.  There doesn't appear to have been any modification at any time.  To the best of my knowledge, this gun is chambered in the factory 2 3/4".  I have not fired this particular gun, though based on condition I wouldn't hesitate to after a qualified smith inspected it.  This is a great example of a Classic Winchester designed shotgun.  It holds up to 6 of the 2 3/4" shells in the tube with no plug installed.  All the parts are forged or machined, and the reason that Winchester quit making it was that it became cost prohibitive and couldn't compete with other manufacturers offerings of the time. (And as we've all heard so many times, they just don't make'em like they used to) I have many pictures available, these ads only allow up to 3 per listing.  I can also take pictures of any areas desired.  $450 cash only, no trades.

Also, I have had several inquiries about shipping this shotgun and out of state buyers wanting to pick it up face to face.  Current BATFE rules and regulations state I CANNOT sell a firearm to anyone not a resident of my home state (GA) without going through a licensed FFL dealer and filling out a form 4473.  I can ship it to your local FFL dealer of choice after receiving a copy of the FFL dealers license, and the buyer will have to pay the $25 outgoing FFL transfer fee from my local dealer.  It is C&R eligible.

Anyone who would like to see this shotgun in person is welcome to email and set up a time to do so.  All meetings to view will take place locally at Bullseye Marksman Gun Club in Cumming, right off GA400 exit 13.  I will need to see at a minimum a GA drivers license.  This shotgun is listed by the BATFE as C&R eligible, so those holding a C&R license may have it shipped directly to them.  Anyone else wanting shipping not holding a C&R license will have to use an FFL licensed dealer.  As long as the ad is still up, the shotgun is still available.
